<item>
            <title>[SPARK-1916] SparkFlumeEvent with body bigger than 1020 bytes are not read properly</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-1916</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The readExternal implementation on SparkFlumeEvent will read only the first 1020 bytes of the actual body when streaming data from flume.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This means that any event sent to Spark via Flume will be processed properly if the body is small, but will fail if the body is bigger than 1020.&lt;br/&gt;
Considering that the default max size for a Flume Avro Event is 32K, the implementation should be updated to read more.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The following is related : &lt;a href=&quot;http://apache-spark-user-list.1001560.n3.nabble.com/Spark-Streaming-using-Flume-body-size-limitation-tt6127.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://apache-spark-user-list.1001560.n3.nabble.com/Spark-Streaming-using-Flume-body-size-limitation-tt6127.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
